### Micronaut HTTP Controller Example

Source: https://github.com/micronaut-projects/micronaut-core/blob/5.1.x/src/main/docs/guide/appendix/architecture/httpServerArch.adoc

A basic Micronaut controller demonstrating how to handle HTTP requests and return responses. Includes necessary imports for a controller.

```java
package example.micronaut.docs.server.intro;

import io.micronaut.http.HttpRequest;
import io.micronaut.http.annotation.Controller;
import io.micronaut.http.annotation.Get;
import io.micronaut.http.annotation.PathVariable;
import io.micronaut.http.annotation.QueryValue;

@Controller("/hello")
public class HelloController {

    @Get
    public String index(@QueryValue(defaultValue = "World") String name) {
        return "Hello " + name;
    }

    @Get("/{name}")
    public String show(@PathVariable String name) {
        return "Hello " + name;
    }
}
```

